FBIS4-19597 "drweu075_i_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-075 Daily Report 18 Apr 1994 FRANCE Mitterand Calls For Revivial of Bosnia Talks Mitterand Calls For Revivial of Bosnia Talks AU1804170394 Paris AFP in English 1648 GMT 18 Apr 94 AU1804170394 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Paris, April 18 (AFP) -- French President Francois Mitterrand urged Monday [18 April] UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali to revive peace talks on Bosnia as soon as possible, a statement from the president's office said. It said Mitterrand, who discussed the current Bosnian crisis with U.S. President Bill Clinton, had sent a message to the U.S. leader as well as to Russian President Boris Yeltsin, Butrus-Ghali and to current European Union President Andreas Papandreou, the premier of Greece.
